\subsection{Product-specific notes}{

\strong{GEDI L1B}: The default set includes \code{rxwaveform}, which is a
\strong{list column} (one numeric vector per shot containing the received
waveform). Use \code{\link[=sl_extract_waveforms]{sl_extract_waveforms()}} to expand this into a
long-form data frame with per-sample elevations. The transmitted
waveform (\code{txwaveform}) is available via explicit request but not
included in defaults. L1B reads are slower than other products
because waveform data requires targeted chunk reads into the pool
dataset.

\strong{GEDI L2A}: The \code{rh} column is a 2D dataset [N, 101] that
expands into 101 columns (\code{rh0} through \code{rh100}), representing
relative height percentiles in metres. This is included in the
default set.

\strong{GEDI L2B}: The default set includes \code{cover_z}, \code{pai_z}, and
\code{pavd_z}, which are 2D datasets [N, 30] representing canopy
vertical profiles at 5 m height bins. Each expands to 30 columns
(e.g. \code{cover_z0} through \code{cover_z29}), adding 90 columns to the
output. \code{pgap_theta_z} is a variable-length list column (similar to
L1B waveforms) and is not included in defaults; request it
explicitly when needed.

\strong{GEDI L2B \code{rh100}}: Stored in centimetres in the HDF5 file;
automatically converted to metres for consistency with L2A.

\strong{GEDI L4A}: The \code{agbd} column is above-ground biomass density in
Mg/ha. Prediction intervals (\code{agbd_pi_lower}, \code{agbd_pi_upper}) and
standard error (\code{agbd_se}) are included in defaults.

\strong{ICESat-2 ATL03}: Photon-level data. A single granule can produce
millions of rows. Multi-granule reads may be slow or timeout due to
the large lat/lon arrays that must be downloaded for spatial
filtering. Use a small bounding box and few granules.
\code{signal_conf_ph} is a 2D column [N, 5] (5 surface types: land,
ocean, sea ice, land ice, inland water) that expands to 5 columns.

\strong{ICESat-2 ATL06}: Land ice elevation segments. The default set
includes fit statistics (\code{n_fit_photons}, \code{h_robust_sprd}, \code{snr})
and reference DEM height (\code{dem_h}). Tidal and geophysical
corrections are available via \code{sl_columns("ATL06")} but not in
defaults.

\strong{ICESat-2 ATL08}: The default set includes \code{canopy_h_metrics}, a
2D dataset [N, 18] of canopy height percentiles (P10 through P95)
that expands to 18 columns. Terrain slope, photon counts, and land
cover are also included. The \verb{*_20m} sub-segment columns and
\verb{*_abs} (absolute height) variants are available but not in
defaults.
